<!doctype html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>Russell Dudek | Candidate Vision for Director, Artificial Intelligence Technology</title><meta name="description" content="An independent candidate vision for enterprise AI technology leadership at Universal Orlando Resort."><link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"></head><body><a class="skip-link" href="#main">Skip to content</a><nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Primary"><a class="nav-name" href="index.html">Russell Dudek <span>/ Candidate Vision</span></a><div class="nav-links"><a href="#mandate">Mandate</a><a href="#system">Operating model</a><a href="#evidence">Evidence</a><a href="#entry">120 days</a><a href="resume.html">Resume</a></div></nav><main id="main">
<section class="hero"><div class="hero-copy"><div class="company-lockup"><img src="assets/brand/universal-orlando-logo.png" alt="Universal Orlando Resort"><div class="company-lockup-text">Candidate vision for<br>Director, Artificial Intelligence Technology<br>by Russell Dudek</div></div><p class="eyebrow">Enterprise AI for a live experience business</p><h1>The model is <em>not</em> the show.</h1><p class="hero-deck">The guest experience is. Build AI so it becomes invisible in the moment - and legible in the operation.</p><div class="hero-actions"><a class="btn primary" href="#system">Explore the AI Show Contract</a><a class="btn" href="resume.html">View role-aligned resume</a></div></div>
<div class="show-stage" aria-labelledby="show-title"><div class="show-stage-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">Interactive operating artifact</p><h2 id="show-title">AI Show Contract</h2></div><span class="show-state" id="show-state">Show ready</span></div><div class="stage-window" aria-label="Four aligned operating books"><div class="stage-floor"></div><article class="scene-flat" data-book="scene" data-health="green"><small>Book 01</small><strong>Scene</strong><p>Outcome, owner and baseline for a specific guest or business moment.</p></article><article class="scene-flat" data-book="cue" data-health="green"><small>Book 02</small><strong>Cue</strong><p>Data context, model role, human authority and decision boundaries.</p></article><article class="scene-flat" data-book="run" data-health="green"><small>Book 03</small><strong>Run</strong><p>Testing, MLOps, observability, security, rollback and partner resilience.</p></article><article class="scene-flat" data-book="review" data-health="green"><small>Book 04</small><strong>Review</strong><p>Adoption, ROI, trust, incidents, learning and reuse or retirement.</p></article></div><div class="stage-controls"><div class="scenario-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Operating scenarios"><button role="tab" aria-selected="true" data-scenario="steady">Steady state</button><button role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-scenario="arrival">Peak arrival</button><button role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-scenario="disruption">Attraction disruption</button><button role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-scenario="drift">Model drift</button><button role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-scenario="vendor">Vendor API outage</button></div><div class="scenario-readout"><p id="scenario-copy" aria-live="polite"><strong>Decision:</strong> All four books agree. Release remains observable, reversible and owned.</p><button class="restore-btn" id="restore" type="button">Restore continuity</button></div></div></div></section>
<section class="section light" id="mandate"><p class="section-kicker">Why this role matters now</p><h2>A larger universe raises the cost of invisible failure.</h2><p class="section-lede">Universal Orlando is operating a four-park destination after Epic Universe doubled the resort footprint, while its parent is expanding new experience formats and markets. More guest moments, digital touchpoints, vendors and operating dependencies increase both AI opportunity and the consequence of weak production discipline.</p><div class="moment-grid"><div class="moment-facts"><div class="fact"><b>4 parks</b><span>The official resort site now presents a four-park vacation portfolio.</span></div><div class="fact"><b>750 acres</b><span>Epic Universe added a major new operating footprint, according to Reuters.</span></div><div class="fact"><b>$7B est.</b><span>Reuters reported an estimated investment of roughly $7 billion.</span></div><div class="fact"><b>24/7 stakes</b><span>Guest experience, operations, commerce, hotels and support do not behave like a lab environment.</span></div></div><div><p class="mandate">The real mandate is to turn fragmented AI demand into a production system that creates measurable value across parks, hotels, digital, marketing and enterprise operations - while protecting continuity, privacy, resilience, human authority and trust.</p><span class="hypothesis-tag">Candidate hypothesis for discovery</span></div></div></section>
<section class="section dark"><p class="section-kicker">The operating contradictions</p><h2>AI leadership lives between applause and interruption.</h2><div class="tension-table"><div class="tension-row"><strong>Immersive guest experience</strong><span>must coexist with</span><strong>Invisible technical and operational risk</strong></div><div class="tension-row"><strong>Rapid opportunity capture</strong><span>must coexist with</span><strong>Privacy, safety, security and governance</strong></div><div class="tension-row"><strong>Enterprise standards</strong><span>must coexist with</span><strong>Domain judgment in parks, hotels, marketing and operations</strong></div><div class="tension-row"><strong>Model performance in development</strong><span>must coexist with</span><strong>Peak-demand reliability, recovery and edge cases</strong></div><div class="tension-row"><strong>Vendor acceleration</strong><span>must coexist with</span><strong>Internal ownership, API resilience and exit paths</strong></div></div></section>
